## Standard Workflow

### 1. Development (Desktop/projects)

```bash
cd ~/Desktop/projects/unified-manager

# Make changes to files...

git add <changed-files>
git commit -m "feat: your feature description"
git push origin main
```

### 2. Deploy to Production (~/.pi/agent)

```bash
cd ~/.pi/agent/skills/unified-manager && git pull
cd ~/.pi/agent/extensions/dashboard-tools && git pull
cd ~/.pi/agent/extensions/issue-tracker && git pull
```

### 3. Quick Sync (All Production Installs)

```bash
for dir in \
  ~/.pi/agent/skills/unified-manager \
  ~/.pi/agent/extensions/dashboard-tools \
  ~/.pi/agent/extensions/issue-tracker; do
  cd "$dir" && git pull
done
```

## Commit Message Format

```
<type>: <short description>

[Optional: Detailed changes]
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`

**Examples:**
```
feat: Add task_delete tool with confirmation

fix: Prevent race condition in state persistence
- Add mutex lock around file writes
- Add retry logic for failed writes
```

## If You Accidentally Edit ~/.pi/agent

```bash
cd ~/.pi/agent/skills/unified-manager
git checkout -- .
git pull origin main
```

## Emergency: Full Reset

```bash
cd ~/.pi/agent/skills
rm -rf unified-manager
git clone https://github.com/slyfornAI/unified-manager.git
```
